column1: (Note: S: surface water sample, B: bottom water sample; cell concentration (including in the supplemental tables) is cells per liter of water (Cells/L)
column2: Cell abundance (cells/L). Note: In this report, when a species' cell abundance is 4-7 e^5 cells/L, it is called a minor bloom; when the concentration is 7-13 e^5 cells/L, it is a regular bloom; if it is >13 e^5 cells/L, it is considered a major bloom. When the total cell abundance is 3-6 e^5 cells/L, it is considered a low cell abundance; when the concentration is < 3 e^5 cells/L, it is considered a very low cell abundance.
